==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old High German [[blozan]], Old Norse [[blóta]] (Swedish [[blota]]), Gothic [[𐌱𐌻𐍉𐍄𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'blo:tan/

===Verb===
'''blōtan''' (class VII strong)
# to [[sacrifice]]
#:''Ure yldran on ðam monþe bleoton a'': our forefathers always sacrificed in this month.

